review_text:

Food is good usually good though in recent months the staff appear to be very overworked, food takes a good 25 minutes at the drive thru for the last few visits, a couple of weeks back we were sat in the car park nearly an hour before getting to the window. Steadily going downhill for a while. I don't blame the staff, as there should be more staff in the restaurant to cope with demand. During my last visit I counted atleast 10 orders on screen at 11am.

At my last visit staff member dropped drink on floor out the drive thru window and didn't offer replacement , very disappointing. One person left with the drink that was paid for.

We usually travel once a week from Scarborough to do shopping at ASDA across the road and get taco bell for dinner on the way home, about 50 miles each way, I think we might be giving it a skip for the next couple months and try McDonald's next door instead.

Hopefully things will improve in a month or two.

name: Taco Bell
review_text: The restraint was clean and their was excellent customer service. However, the food wasn't very nice to be honest. The tacos weren't special; standard tacos shell standard beef and some lettuce. The Mexican fries where on first impression differently nice but after a few more, the sickly powdered cheese on them made them unable to eat personally. I also got cheesy fries desperately to try and although there was plenty of cheese, the cheese was disgusting, DISGUSTING. It was plastic cheese often found on a burger melted with a dollop of tasteless sour cream. Note to self don't get anything with "cheese" on again. On the up side there was bottomless soft drinks! That watered down the foul taste of the cheese you fries. The churros where... alright even though they are traditionally Spanish and taco bell is Mexican. In conclusion, I would give more stars due to a good atmosphere however the disappointing food let it down a lot. I expected good things but in the end I reached an anticlimactic solution. Go to taco bell but only if you like these very Americanly adapted flavours.
